# Testing Conventions

## Test pyramid
- Unit tests (`tests/unit/`) — fast, isolated, no I/O. One test file per source module.
- Integration tests (`tests/integration/`) — test composed behavior; real DB/API calls allowed.
- E2E acceptance tests (`tests/e2e/`) — one spec file per feature, scenarios map 1:1 to acceptance scenarios in `requirements.md`.

## Naming conventions
- Test files: `<module>.test.ts` or `<module>.test.tsx`
- Describe blocks: name of the module or component under test.
- Test names: `should <expected behavior> when <condition>`.

## TDD cycle enforcement
1. Write a test that describes the next required behavior.
2. Run it. It must fail (red).
3. Write only enough code to pass it (green).
4. Refactor with tests green.
5. Commit only when all tests pass.

## Rules
- No `test.skip` or `test.todo` in committed code without a linked issue.
- No `jest.mock` for modules you own — use dependency injection instead.
- Assertions must be specific: prefer `toEqual({ id: 1, name: "Alice" })` over `toBeTruthy()`.
- Every bug fix starts with a failing regression test.
